
# Jira Installation And License Configuration <a id="Jira-Installation-And-License-Configuration"></a>

To install Jira on Windows, follow these steps. Jira provides an official package that simplifies the installation process.

> **NOTE:** JRE SHOULD BE ALREADY INSTALLED ON YOUR SYSTEM. IF IT'S NOT, INSTALL IT FIRST!  
> **NOTE:** Install from [Atlassian Jira Download](https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/download).  
> Install this versioon `Jira Software 8.1`.

### Steps:

1. Install JIRA Software as a service (By Default).  
   **DO NOT RUN JIRA AFTER INSTALLATION** (Untick "Start" AT THE END OF SETUP).

2. Copy `atlassian-agent.jar` to the root of drive `C:\`  
   So it will be: `C:\atlassian-agent.jar`

3. From the Start menu, search for CMD & open it.

   3.1. Type `CD <bin directory of your Jira installation>` & press Enter.  
   If installed in the default directory, it will be:  
   `cd C:\Program Files\Atlassian\Jira\bin`

4. From the Start menu, search for **Services** & open it.

   4.1. Find **Atlassian Jira Service**, double-click on it, and copy the Service Name  
   (Example: `JiraSoftware060122091949`). Close this window.

   4.2. Type `tomcat9w //ES//<Service Name>` & press Enter.  or tomcat8w
   Example: `tomcat9w //ES//JiraSoftware060122091949`

5. In the **Atlassian Jira Properties** window, go to the **Java** tab and add  
   `-javaagent:C:\atlassian-agent.jar` to the end of **Java Options**. Click OK and close CMD.

6. From the Start menu, search for **Stop Jira Service** & run it. Then, search for **Start Jira Service** & run it.  
   Afterward, right-click on **Atlassian Jira Service** (in the Services window) & select Start (if available).

7. Run Jira from `http://localhost:8080/` (Or access Jira from the Start menu).  
   If it's not accessible, wait a few minutes & try again later.

8. Choose **I'll Set it Up Myself** and click **Next**, then provide the SQLServer database credentials.  
   For the type, choose **My Own Database**.

   > [Steps to Create SQL Server Database for Jira](../Steps_to_Create_SQL_Server_Database_for_Jira/Steps_to_Create_SQL_Server_Database_for_Jira.md)

9. When asked for a license, open CMD.

note 1 :From the search menu, search for and run **Environment Variables**. Then, in the **User variables** section, click on **New**, enter `JIRA_HOME` for the name and `jira-installation-directory\atlassian-jira\WEB-INF\classes` for the value. 

`jira-installation-directory` is the software installation location on your system. If installed in the default path, this value will be as follows:

cd C:\Program Files\Atlassian\Jira

note 2 : From the search menu, search for and run **Environment Variables**. Then, in the **System variables** section, click on **New**, enter `path` for the name and for example `C:\Program Files (x86)\Common Files\Oracle\Java\javapath` for the value. 
if `path` exist just edit and add the value.


   9.1. Type `CD C:\` & press Enter.  
   9.2. Type `java -jar atlassian-agent.jar -m <your email> -o <your organization> -p <product to activate> -s <Server ID>` & press Enter.  
   Example for JIRA Software:  
   `java -jar atlassian-agent.jar -m downloadly@somemail.com -o souud -p jira -s BOUT-MSPD-VUPT-3PYD`

   > **NOTE 1:** Server ID is shown during the License request step on the JIRA Setup wizard.  
   > **NOTE 2:** Product codes & additional parameters can be obtained by executing `java -jar atlassian-agent.jar`.

   9.3. Copy the produced license to the Jira License request field.

10. **ENJOY!**

---

> **NOTE:** If you installed JIRA without a service, adding a javaagent requires different steps.  
> You can find the corresponding steps by searching on the web (e.g., "how to add javaagent to Jira `<product>` `<platform>` without service").  
> Once the javaagent is configured, follow step 6 above!
